# Model Config Block Checklist

## Required Config Properties (All Models)

- [ ] `schema` ‚Äî matches the Dune app schema name
- [ ] `alias` ‚Äî matches the Dune app table/view name
- [ ] `materialized` ‚Äî explicitly declared (`view`, `table`, or `incremental`)

## Additional Requirements by Materialization

### `table`
- [ ] `file_format='delta'`

### `incremental`
- [ ] `file_format='delta'`
- [ ] `incremental_strategy` ‚Äî `merge` (standard), `append` (rare), or `delete+insert` (rare)
- [ ] `unique_key` ‚Äî single column or list. No NULLs allowed in these columns.
- [ ] `incremental_predicates` ‚Äî use the macro: `[incremental_predicate('DBT_INTERNAL_DEST.block_time')]`
  - Only for time-series data. Omit when full-history lookups are needed (e.g., pool creation).
- [ ] If partitioned: partition column(s) included in `unique_key`

## Partition Patterns

- `partition_by=['block_month']` ‚Äî most common (trades, transfers, swaps)
- `partition_by=['block_date']` ‚Äî very high-volume tables
- `partition_by=['blockchain', 'project', 'block_month']` ‚Äî cross-chain sector spells
- Only partition if each partition will have 1M+ rows

## Optional Properties

- `post_hook` ‚Äî for `expose_spells` / `optimize_spell` on final lineage models
- `tags` ‚Äî `'prod_exclude'` for failing/excluded models, `'static'` for hardcoded data tables
- `on_table_exists` ‚Äî rare, usually applied by the Dune team

## Config Block Format

```sql
{{ config(
	schema='my_schema',
	alias='my_alias',
	materialized='incremental',
	file_format='delta',
	incremental_strategy='merge',
	unique_key=['block_date', 'tx_hash', 'evt_index'],
	incremental_predicates=[incremental_predicate('DBT_INTERNAL_DEST.block_time')],
	post_hook='{{ expose_spells(\'["ethereum"]\', "project", "my_project", \'["contributor"]\') }}',
) }}
```

## Incremental Model Body

- Use `{% if is_incremental() -%}` (trailing `-` only) to split logic:
  - **Incremental path**: Apply `{{ incremental_predicate('source.block_time') }}` on sources
  - **Non-incremental path**: Filter from earliest date of activity (`block_date >= timestamp '2020-01-01'`)
- Apply incremental filters on ALL time-series sources in the query

## Directory Conventions

- **Sector-level** (dedicated sub-project): `dbt_subprojects/<project>/models/<alias>/<blockchain>/platforms/`
- **Sector-level** (daily/hourly): `dbt_subprojects/<project>/models/_sector/<sector>/<alias>/<blockchain>/`
- **Project-level**: `dbt_subprojects/<project>/models/_project/<project_name>/<blockchain>/`

## File Naming

- Format: `<project_version_blockchain_alias.sql>` (e.g., `uniswap_v3_arbitrum_base_trades.sql`)
- File name = model name in dbt
- One model per file
